--complexity is the more the norm than the exception. And not by happenstance, but by design.--Sure, we know what mechanism can cause the apparent design of complexity. --Now let's see, 100 billion galaxies ... but nah, mankind is the only intelligent being in existence. --That we know of. It's called selection bias.ID speculates on lack of evidence to suggest that our ignorance is best explained by something called design. Let's not confuse the matter by claiming that ID postulates anything relevant to science.